sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K094141
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This LacI gene contains a mutated pLacIq promoter which enables high level of transcription. This ensures effective repression of pLacI promoter that might be present.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Liu Chenli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Comes from E. Coli strain DH10B genomic sequence, with a point mutation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This device may have very strong repression on pLacI controlled operons.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K094142
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is composited with a lacI operon and an mRFP operon. The LacI operon contains a mutated lacIq promoter that enables high level of transcription. The mRFP operon is spontaneously repressed by the LacI operon, and can be turned on by inducing with IPTG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Shi Lei

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K094140
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: mutant promoter of lacI gene, which enables high level of lacI protein expression
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Liu Chenli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: point mutation made from E. Coli genomic lacI gene promoter
